text: Jean-Jacques Honorat (April 1, 1931 - July 26, 2023) was a Haitian politician. He was named Prime Minister of Haiti after René Préval was removed following President Jean-Bertrand Aristide removal by a coup in October 1991. He resigned from the office eight months later on June 19, 1992.
